  "statement": {
    "markdown": "An artist is planning to paint a rectangular room with a robot that follows a grid path. The grid is represented as a matrix of 0s and 1s, where 0s represent open spaces and 1s represent walls. The robot starts at the top-left corner of the grid and can move in four directions: up, down, left, right. The robot can only paint a cell when it reaches it. The cost of painting a cell is equal to the sum of all costs of its ancestors. Your task is to find the minimum total cost to paint all reachable cells from the top-left corner.",
    "inputFormat": "The input is a matrix of 0s and 1s, where each matrix element is an integer representing the cost of painting that cell.",
    "outputFormat": "Output the minimum total cost to paint all reachable cells from the top-left corner.",
